# Social SaaS Project Structure

## Overview
This is a modern SaaS application for social media management built with Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Supabase.

## Directory Structure
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router pages
│   ├── dashboard/         # Dashboard pages and features
│   │   └── page.tsx       # Main dashboard page
│   ├── globals.css        # Global styles and Tailwind imports
│   ├── layout.tsx         # Root layout with metadata
│   └── page.tsx           # Landing page
├── components/            # React components
│   ├── auth/             # Authentication components
│   │   └── auth-form.tsx  # Login/signup form
│   └── ui/               # Shadcn/UI components
└── lib/                  # Utility functions and configurations
    ├── supabase.ts       # Supabase client and types
    └── utils.ts          # Utility functions
```

## Key Files
- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with metadata
- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Landing page with hero section
- [src/app/dashboard/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/dashboard/page.tsx) - Main dashboard
- [src/components/auth/auth-form.tsx](mdc:src/components/auth/auth-form.tsx) - Authentication form
- [src/lib/supabase.ts](mdc:src/lib/supabase.ts) - Supabase configuration

## Configuration Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - Shadcn/UI configuration
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project documentation

## Development Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Follow Next.js 15 App Router conventions
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Implement proper error handling
- Follow Supabase best practices for database operations

